Anglican Archbishop Thabo Makgoba says those who have stolen money, have denied the poor the means of coping with the pandemic. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Anglican Archbishop Thabo Makgoba's used his Easter sermon to lament corruption during the COVID-19 pandemic. He says those who have stolen money, have denied the poor the means of coping with the pandemic. READ: Churches prepare for Easter Makgoba was speaking during the Easter Vigil at St George's Cathedral in Cape Town. Watch the video above.